<paragraph id="CONSTITUTION_27" base="F22464542"><paranum>27</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS Foundation"/><data name="paranum" value="27"/></prolog><body><p id="CONSTITUTION_P0074" outputclass="keep_with_next">In a manner consistent with the &#x2018;Criteria                         for IASB members&#x2019; as set out in the <xref href="CONSTITUTION_ANNEX.dita#CONSTITUTION_ANNEX">Annex to this                                         <i>Constitution</i></xref> and in order to ensure a broad                         international balance, there shall normally be:</p><ol id="CONSTITUTION_L0008" base="F22464544" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value>                                 <p id="CONSTITUTION_P0075" base="F22464545">four members from the                                         Asia-Oceania region;</p></li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value>                                 <p id="CONSTITUTION_P0076" base="F22464547">four members from                                         Europe;</p></li><li><li_value>(c)</li_value>                                 <p id="CONSTITUTION_P0077" base="F22464549">four members from the                                         Americas;</p></li><li><li_value>(d)</li_value>                                 <p id="CONSTITUTION_P0078" base="F22464551">one member from Africa;                                         and</p></li><li><li_value>(e)</li_value>                                 <p id="CONSTITUTION_P0080" base="F22464555">one member appointed                                         from any area, subject to maintaining overall geographical                                         balance.</p></li></ol><p id="CONSTITUTION_P0081" base="F22464556">The work of the IASB shall not be invalidated by its                         failure at any time to have a full complement of members according to the                         above geographical allocation, although the Trustees shall use their best                         endeavours to achieve the geographical allocation.</p></body></paragraph>